+
+// Both goroutines wait on `deadline` to stop — but `deadline = time.after(...)`
+// is a one-shot, receive-only source: its single value reaches ONE `<-deadline`,
+// so the other goroutine hangs forever (the real deadlock this example avoids by
+// broadcasting). Stating the intent `deadline delivered-to-all { producer,
+// consumer }` makes the coverage static arm reject it — a RecvChan cannot broadcast.
+contract RateLimited {
+  participant producer
+  participant consumer
+  channel deadline
+  deadline delivered-to-all { producer, consumer }
+}
